"Captain Corelli's Mandolin" by Louis de Bernieres
==================================================
Reading, UK, 1994

(not sure if that is Vintage International Paperback, 1994)


p.205: This was not what she expected, but nonetheless (* HER HEART GALLOPED
PAINFULLY WITH FEAR AND ANXIETY *) , and a sensation of extreme dread rendered
her momentarily speechless; 'I was washing it', she said feebly at last.

p.278: The doctor was surprised.  'What do I want to talk to her about? (* HE
ASKED HIMSELF *) .It was as if he had (* GLEANED SOME IMPRESSIONS *), some
impressions that needed to be discussed, but which had not yet (* CONGEALED
INTO A SET OF IDEAS. *)
